ABOUT US
J.D. IRVING, LIMITED
MILESTONES
VISION & PURPOSE
VALUES

Welcome
to Irving Consumer Products

					We're glad you're interested in our organization. Irving Consumer Products Limited. is one of North America's leading manufacturers of premium quality private label & store brand household paper products, baby diapers, and children's training pants.
					We also proudly manufacture some of the most recognizable, top-selling paper product brands in both Canada and the United States.
					If you're interested in joining the Irving Consumer Products Limited. family, or to learn more about other career opportunities with J.D. Irving, Limited
					 
CLICK HERE
				 

				 


		 


Proudly part ofJ.D. Irving Group of CompaniesJ.D. Irving, Limited is a family-owned company that employs over 15,000 people throughout North America. Forestry, food, shipbuilding and transportation are just a few of the business segments they operate in.
					 

CONSUMER PRODUCTSProudly manufacturing premium household paper products, baby diapers and training pants for North American markets.
						 

SHIPBUILDING, INDUSTRIAL & CONSTRUCTIONIrving Shipbuilding Inc. provides shipbuilding and repair, drill rig construction and conversion, offshore fabrication, industrial manufacturing, engineering, supply chain management and quality and technical services.
						 

RETAIL & DISTRIBUTIONOur retail and distribution companies provide consumer, contractor and business solutions, with quality supplies and services.
						 

FOREST PRODUCTSSustainable forest management is our commitment to both our customers and the environment.
						 

TRANSPORTATIONOur transportation companies provide courier, trucking, rail, tug, barge, ocean towing, offshore supply and deep-sea shipping for general goods and specialized cargoes.
						 

FOOD PRODUCTSCavendish Group produces frozen and fresh potato products and appetizers for retail, quick service restaurants and food service operations throughout North America.
						 






Major Milestones


						 
Saint John Paper MillIrving Tissue begins with the purchase of a paper mill in Saint John, New Brunswick. This new mill produces jumbo rolls of tissue, which are converted into quality consumer products.



				
					 


						 
Dieppe Tissue PlantConstruction is complete on Irving Tissue's first tissue converting plant in Dieppe, New Brunswick. Production begins for private label products and the new Canadian brand Majesta® is launched in Canada.
							
							 



					 


						 
Fort Edward Tissue PlantIrving Tissue acquires a paper mill and tissue converting facility in Fort Edward, New York. Irving also acquires the right to market Scotties® Facial Tissue in the USA.
							
							 



					 


						 
Toronto Tissue Plant
							Irving Tissue expands yet again and acquires
							a tissue mill and converting facility in Toronto, Ontario. Irving also acquires the rights to market the Royale® brand in Canada.
							
							 



					 


						 
Diapers & Training Pants
							 Irving Personal Care opens a new state-of-the-art plant in New Brunswick, Canada to produce premium quality private label baby diapers and training pant products for major North American retailers.
							
							 



					 


						 
TAD Technology
							 Major investments were made in the Irving Tissue plant in Fort Edward, NY.  Along with a building addition, a new through-air-dried (TAD) paper machine is installed, increasing capacity and product quality.
							
							 



					 













		 


 
