                                            Irvin John Borchers, U.S. Navy, ret.Age 82, born Sept. 25, 1921 in Detroit, Michigan.  Passed away Oct. 30, 2003 in Shoreline, WA.  At 17, Johnny graduated from high school class of 1940 and joined the U.S. Navy. In 1958, he married Fuku Nomura in Fukuoka, Japan.  In 1962, he retired from the Navy as an E-6, BM1c. In 1962, he worked as a security guard for Pinkerton.He then worked for the civil service as Asst. Lockmaster at the Government Locks ? Ballard and retired in 1976.  He enjoyed fishing, golfing, long mall walks and the company of his many friends.His beloved wife Fuku, a cousin William Daley and longtime friends: John and Masako Connor, Tom and June Hurst, Linda Okano and Sue Smith survive him.By his request, a family only inurnment will be held at Evergreen Memorial Park 206-362-5200.  Memorials preferred to 911-Lynnwood Fire Station or Swedish Hospital. 





